data.text:
1922

1 hr 16 mins

Comedy

NR

Watchlist

A compelling character study of an old Parisian peddler (Maurice de Feraudy) whose fortunes change after he gets arrested following a run-in with a gendarme. Jean Forest. Written and directed by Jacques Feyder, who adapted a novel by Anatole France. Also known as "Bill."
